msgstr "‘Form is my self,’ do you have power over that form to say: "

msgctxt "mn35:15.4"
msgid "evaṃ me rūpaṃ hotu, evaṃ me rūpaṃ mā ahosī”ti? "
msgstr "‘May my form be like this! May it not be like that’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn35:15.5"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”. "
msgstr "“No, Master Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya16, sc14
msgctxt "mn35:16.1"
msgid "“Manasi karohi, aggivessana; "
msgstr "“Think about it, Aggivessana! "

# NOTE: Here neither attention nor focus suits manasikara. The Buddha is telling Saccaka to recollect an earlier statement when making a later one, i.e. to practice basic rationality.
msgctxt "mn35:16.2"
msgid "manasi karitvā kho, aggivessana, byākarohi. "
msgstr "You should think before answering. "

msgctxt "mn35:16.3"
msgid "Na kho te sandhiyati purimena vā pacchimaṃ pacchimena vā purimaṃ. "
msgstr "What you said before and what you said after don’t match up. "

msgctxt "mn35:16.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, aggivessana, "
msgstr "What do you think, Aggivessana? "

msgctxt "mn35:16.5"
msgid "yaṃ tvaṃ evaṃ vadesi: "
msgstr "When you say, "

